snippet.textDisplay: I remember starting my first year in high school in 2011. All my spare time was used just riding my bmx around. I remember a friend showed me Nike’s on my feet and best day ever. I would then spend the next few months, listening to those and all the other amazing Mac songs just riding my bike around and just absorbing all his music. I remember waking up one morning, scrolled through Instagram, saw post’s saying “rest in peace Mac”. I couldn’t believe what I was seeing, spent the rest of that day questioning why it happened to him? I remember it rained all day long. Anyways Mac, thank you for creating music. Music that takes me back to being a kid, i am 21 now, turning 22 soon. I’ll always listen to your music no matter how old I am. Miss you. Hope everything is okay up there. ❤️❤️

snippet.textDisplay:
[Verse 1]
Yeah, it's been a while without your face
But I saw your picture on the wall the other day
Too much distance, too much space
You need to come back home and run along, yeah
I'm waiting for the light to change
You ask me how I've been and I'm good, I can't complain
Times get harder, things get strange
All I know, I don't want you gone

[Chorus]
I know it hasn't been easy lately
But you don't want to leave me, baby
And you know I hate to keep you waiting
But when it's right, girl, it's right, yeah

[Post-Chorus]
Days turn into nights
Conversations turn into fights, we gon' be alright
Love turn into life
Girl, you been burnin' so bright, let me turn off the lights
Stay awake 'til the mornin', yeah
It ain't always great, but it's never borin', yeah

[Verse 2]
And I been itching for your love
Don't want to feel a single thing if it ain't your touch
I get drunk and become none
Just want to stumble into us
But baby, don't stop now 'cause it ain't over, yeah
Three years ago I was so dumb
Clueless, young and stupid, but look at who I have become
I ain't gonna break your heart, promise it's always safe
Baby, don't go now, pull me closer

[Chorus]

But you don't want to leave me, baby (Woah)
You know I hate to keep you waiting

[Outro]

snippet.textDisplay: My dad about three years ago told me about Mac and I ignored him thinking that he was just another artist. Then after he passed I still didn't listen and I don't know why. But when circles came out and i thought "sure I'll listen" didn't think it would break me down after the third song. It was beautiful and then I listened to swimming and now I feel bad that I didn't listen to him while he was alive. But I am glad all of this was released or I would not be listening to his or I might not be here now typing this. Thanks Mac you help me stop cutting. Love you Mac
